[Dispensation by Peter, cardinal-priest of St. Praxed’s—in virtue of a bnll of Benedict XII, dated 25 June, 1337, empowering him and his fellow-nuncio Bertrand, cardinal-deacon of St. Mary’s in Aquiro, during their mission to France and Enghrnd, to dispense 100 illegitimate clerks, not born of married parents, to receive ordination—to Richard Aleyn of Cuxton, son of Simon de Bradestede‚ to be ordained and hold a benefice with cure, not in a cathedra] church, on the usual conditions; Richard is the sixty-eighth clerk dispensed]

Petrus miseracione divina tituli sancte Praxedis presbyter car- dinalis, apostolice sedis nuncius, dilecto nobis in Christo Ricardo Aleyn de Cuklestane‚ nato Symonis de Bradestede, clerico Roffensis diocesis, salutem in domino. Sanctissimus pater et dominus noster, dominus Benedictus divina providencia papa XII, nos ad Francie et Anglie partes pro magnis et arduis negociis destinando, patentes literas apostolicas ejus vera bulla plumbea bullatas nobis in hac forma¹ concessit:—

1337· June 24.

Benedictus episcopus, servus servorum dei, dilectis filiis Petro tituli sancte Praxedis presbytero, et Bertrando sancte Marie in Aquiro diacono, cardinalibus, apostolice sedis nunciis, salutem et apostolicam benediccionem.
